            <pre>
                <div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: -200px;">
                <div style="display: inline-block; text-align: left;">
    
            
                <font size="5.5px">
            
    A cookie is a small file kept on your computer with an identification code 
    specific to your computer. When you visit a website the site uses this cookie 
    to keep track of what you've been doing during your visit. So for example, if you're 
    doing some online shopping the website can remember what's in your shopping basket 
    or what you've searched for and then recommend similar items to you. 
    Cookies can also be used to remember your login details, which can be very helpful, or a 
    breach of your privacy depending on how the website chooses to use your information.
                
                 </font>
            
                </div>
                </div>
            </pre>
        
        
    
